body:
@raphinesse I will try to take a look at those tickets tomorrow that you linked for review and opinions.
 
- For https://github.com/apache/cordova/issues/32, I also seen this. I looked into it before and it should be a one liner to delete.

- As for the `package-lock.json`, IMO I would commit it. I don't really experience the negative affects that everyone else seems experience so much. I have actually seen more positive cases. For example: the recent CI tests failure because one of the dependency updated and it had an issue. Locally, it passed because I had the lock. Anyways its just my opinion.

@erisu Yes, #32 should be straightfwd. Just needs to be done, and I'm already distracting myself too much :sweat_smile:.

Re package-lock: I don't care either way for the coming release. Downside is, it's another thing to be done.

I forgot about https://github.com/apache/cordova-common/pull/50 in my previous post. Would be nice to have this in the coming release. I think it's good to go as is, but its verification has been stalled by our uncovering of various Windows issues. Since `cordova-common` will be the first release to do, our schedule might be too tight to squeeze in this change.
